# Goose Operations Runbook

Canonical runbook for the Goose 1.x CLI execution surface on Mac Studio Ollama.

**Deployed shape (verified 2026-05-03):**
- Provider: `ollama` (native, direct — no litellm hop)
- Model: `qwen3-coder:30b`
- Host: `mac-studio.internal:11434`
- Config: `~/.config/goose/config.yaml` (operator-local) or `config/goose/config.yaml` (repo-tracked)

## 1. Invocation

Invoke `goose` directly — no launcher needed. Provider/model/host are read from `~/.config/goose/config.yaml` at startup.

Workflow:
```bash
# Edit repo-tracked config
vim config/goose/config.yaml

# Sync to operator-local
cp config/goose/config.yaml ~/.config/goose/config.yaml

# Invoke Goose
goose
```

## 2. Capability posture

**Read-only substrate only.** Operator review is mandatory on all output.

Disabled extensions (capability-validation phase):
- `developer` (shell exec + file write)
- `summon` (subagent delegation)
- `apps` (sandboxed HTML/CSS/JS apps)
- `chatrecall` (past-conversation search)
- `summarize` (LLM summary bypass)
- `tom` (top-of-mind injection)
- `code_execution` (tool elision)
- `orchestrator` (multi-agent session management)

Enabled extensions:
- `filesystem-mcp` (repo read access)
- `xindex` (service registry read)
- `todo`, `analyze`, `skills`, `extensionmanager` (platform)

See `docs/architecture-facts/goose-capability-boundary.md` for full posture and Phase-A promotion gate.

## 3. Common failure modes

### 3.1 DNS cache issues (mac-studio.internal)
```bash
# Clear mDNS cache
sudo killall -HUP mDNSResponder
```

### 3.2 Ollama unreachable
```bash
# Verify Ollama is running
curl -v http://mac-studio.internal:11434
# Expected: HTTP/1.1 200 OK
```

### 3.3 Tool-loop hang
- Cancel with `Ctrl+C`
- Restart with `goose`
- Check Ollama health (`curl -v http://mac-studio.internal:11434`)

## 4. Substrate facts

- Mac Studio at `192.168.10.142`
- Ollama version: 0.22.1
- Model: `qwen3-coder:30b`
- Host: `mac-studio.internal:11434`
- Context limit: 32768 tokens

## 5. Security checklist

- [ ] Ensure operator-local config matches repo-tracked config
- [ ] Verify Ollama connectivity: `curl -v http://mac-studio.internal:11434`
- [ ] Operator review mandatory on all output (no platform-state changes from Goose)
- [ ] DNS cache cleared if hostname resolution fails

## 6. Backups

None — no persistent state is maintained. Each session is self-contained.
Configuration is version-controlled in `config/goose/config.yaml`.
